{
  "texts": [
    "We choose the sentence as the main unit of text because papers in metallurgic literature often discuss multiple phases and properties in a single paper.",
    "Focusing on a smaller unit of text reduces the possibilities of ambiguous relationships.",
    "On the other hand considering larger units of text (e.g., paragraph) may challenge extraction of unambiguously coupled phase-property pairs and the sentiment of their relationships.",
    "Furthermore, we hypothesize that the description of phases and their impact on properties is captured at the sentence level in the metallurgical literature at a sufficient level for insights to be gathered.",
    "Finally, focus on a small unit of text enables use of a wide spectrum of NLP tools and LLMs, including those with limited context windows.The prototypical sentence that we targeted to include in the sentence dataset reads as \"[Phase A] leads to an increase in [property B]\"."
  ]
}